definition.value: a cytokine release syndrome AEthat is prolonged (e.g., not rapidly responsive to symptomatic medication and/or brief interruption of infusion); recurrence of symptoms following initial improvement; hospitalization indicated for clinical sequelae (e.g., renal impairment, pulmonary infiltrates)
a dental caries AE that has one or more dental caries, not involving the root
a dental caries AE that has dental caries involving the root
a dental caries AE that has dental caries resulting in pulpitis or periapical abscess or resulting in tooth loss
a device related infection AE where IV antibiotic, antifungal, or antiviral intervention indicated; radiologic or operative intervention indicated
a disseminated intravascular coagulation AE that has laboratory findings with no bleeding
a disseminated intravascular coagulation AE that has laboratory findings and bleeding
an ejection fraction decreased AE where the resting ejection fraction (EF) 50 - 40%; 10 - 19% drop from baseline
an ejection fraction decreased AE where the resting ejection fraction (EF) 39 - 20%; greater than 20% drop from baseline
an ejection fraction decreased AE where the resting ejection fraction (EF) less than 20%
an electrocardiogram qt prolonged AE where the QTc 450 - 480 ms
an electrocardiogram qt prolonged AE where the QTc 481 - 500 ms
an electrocardiogram qt prolonged AE where the QTc is greater than or equal to 501 ms on at least two separate ECGs

an electrocardiogram qt prolonged AE where the QTc is greater than or equal to 501 or greater than 60 ms change from baseline and Torsade de pointes or polymorphic ventricular tachycardia or signs/symptoms of serious arrhythmia
an enterocolitis AE that has abdominal pain; mucus or blood in stool
an enterocolitis AE that has severe or persistent abdominal pain; fever; ileus; peritoneal signs
a fall AE that is minor with no resultant injuries; intervention not indicated
a fall AE where hospitalization indicated

a febrile neutropenia AE categorized as anC less than 1000/mm3 with a single temperature of greater than 38.3 degrees C (101 degrees F) or a sustained temperature of greater than or equal to 38 degrees C (100.4 degrees F) for more than one hour.

label.value: Grade 1 forced expiratory volume decreased AE

definition.value: a forced expiratory volume decreased AE where FEV1% (percentages of observed FEV1 and FVC related to their respective predicted values) 99 - 70% predicted

label.value: Grade 2 forced expiratory volume decreased AE

definition.value: a forced expiratory volume decreased AE where FEV1 60 - 69%

label.value: Grade 3 forced expiratory volume decreased AE

definition.value: a forced expiratory volume decreased AE where FEV1 50 - 59%

label.value: Grade 4 forced expiratory volume decreased AE

definition.value: a forced expiratory volume decreased AE where FEV1 is less than or equal to 49%
a fracture AE that is symptomatic but non-displaced; immobilization indicated
a fracture AE that has severe symptoms; displaced or open wound with bone exposure; disabling; operative intervention indicated
a gamma-glutamyltransferase level increased AE that is greater than the upper limit of normal - 2.5 times upper limit of normal
a gamma-glutamyltransferase level increased AE that is greater than 2.5 - 5.0 times the upper limit of normal
a gamma-glutamyltransferase level increased AE that is greater than 5.0 - 20.0 times the upper limit of normal
a gamma-glutamyltransferase level increased AE that is greater than 20.0 times the upper limit of normal
a gastric ulcer AE that is symptomatic; altered GI function; medical intervention indicated; limiting instrumental activities of daily living
a gastric ulcer AE that has severely altered GI function; TPN indicated; elective operative or endoscopic intervention indicated; limiting self care activities of daily living; disabling
a gastritis AE that is symptomatic; altered GI function; medical intervention indicated
a gastritis AE that has severely altered eating or gastric function; TPN or hospitalization indicated
a hemolytic uremic syndrome AE that has evidence of RBC destruction (schistocytosis) without clinical consequences
a hemolytic uremic syndrome AE that has laboratory findings with clinical consequences (e.g., renal insufficiency, petechiae)
a hemolytic uremic syndrome AE that has life-threatening consequences, (e.g., CNS hemorrhage or thrombosis/embolism or renal failure)
a hemorrhoidal hemorrhage AE where transfusion, radiologic, endoscopic, or elective operative intervention indicated
a hepatic failure AE that has asterixis; mild encephalopathy; limiting self care activities of daily living
a hepatic failure AE that has moderate to severe encephalopathy; coma; life-threatening consequences
a hepatitis viral AE that has symptomatic liver dysfunction; fibrosis by biopsy; compensated cirrhosis; reactivation of chronic hepatitis
a hepatitis viral AE that has decompensated liver function (e.g., ascites, coagulopathy, encephalopathy, coma)
an ileus AE that is symptomatic; altered GI function; bowel rest indicated
an ileus AE that has severely altered GI function; TPN indicated
an infusion related reaction AE that has mild transient reaction; infusion interruption not indicated; intervention not indicated

an infusion related reaction AE where therapy or infusion interruption indicated but responds promptly to symptomatic treatment (e.g., antihistamines, NSAIDS, narcotics, IV fluids); prophylactic medications indicated for less than or equal to 24 hrs

an infusion related reaction AE that is prolonged (e.g., not rapidly responsive to symptomatic medication and/or brief interruption of infusion); recurrence of symptoms following initial improvement; hospitalization indicated for clinical sequelae
an infusion site extravasation AE that has erythema with associated symptoms (e.g., edema, pain, induration, phlebitis)
an infusion site extravasation AE that has ulceration or necrosis; severe tissue damage; operative intervention indicated
an irritability AE that has mild; easily consolable
an irritability AE that has moderate; limiting instrumental activities of daily living; increased attention indicated
